node.text:
With the season in sight, we wanted to share a quick refresher on Priority Reservation Days vs. Week-Of Reservation Days

•Priority Reservation Days: On Nov. 6, you will be able to make reservations for the core season (Dec. 8 – April 4) across all of our resorts. As a pass holder, you can lock in up to 7 Priority Reservation Days for the core season in advance, and as many week-of reservations during the season as your pass type and availability allow.

•Week-Of Reservation Days: As our resorts start to open for the season, you can also take advantage of exclusive early season access by making week-of reservations. Booking a week-of reservation does not count against your Priority Reservation Days for the core season.

Take a sneak peek of our new reservation system at the video above.

node.text: Did you know that each night during the winter season, around 35 snowcats hit the mountain to groom over 115 trails into the corduroy you ski or ride every morning? Watch to learn more about what goes into getting the mountain ready for world class skiing. #EpicTogether

node.text: Unlock the secrets of the past and discover our rich mining, skiing and local history on the Silver to Slopes Historic Mining Tour. Tours depart daily at 10am by the Eagle Statue in Mountain Village and at 1pm at the Trail Map near the top of Bonanza Express. #SilverToSlopes

node.text:
Unlimited Skiing and Riding ✔️ 
20% Discount on Dining, Lodging and Rentals ✔️ 
Memories that will last a lifetime ✔️ 

All of this and more with Epic Mountain Rewards when you purchase a 2021/22 Epic Pass.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Park City on August 19, 2021. May be an image of nature and mountain.

node.text: Taking a moment to share some gratitude today: for the much-needed rain we're having this week, and for the local heroes who have gone above and beyond to protect and support our community throughout the Parley's Canyon Fire. A huge thank you to our first responders, fire crews, emergency management personnel and all the residents, neighbors and friends in the community who have supported evacuees. ⛰❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Park City on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 4 people, people sitting and outdoors.

node.text: Slopeside? Fireside? Why choose? Cozy up with friends at our ski-in-ski-out Mid-Mountain Lodge restaurant for bites and drinks after a great day on the slopes. Plus, 2021/22 Epic Pass holders can enjoy 20% off food all season long.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Park City on August 15, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: There's nothing better than a summer evening stroll down Main Street.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Park City on August 14, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and grass.

node.text:
We are proud to support @recycleutah this weekend at the 6th-annual 100 Mile Meal, a gourmet dinner experience in which all menu ingredients are sourced from within 100 miles of Park City and prepared by our own Park City Mountain expert chefs. 

This unique event is a celebration of our local farmers, ranchers and vendors, and seeks to create a community culture of supporting local food sources and dining more sustainably. #eatlocal #sustainabilitystories

node.text:
Have you made it to the Canyons Village Summer Concert Series yet? We're looking forward to tonight's performance by @taylorscottband and are keeping the good times rolling with @turkuazband this Saturday.

And because we can't get enough of the fun, we've extended the Summer Concert Series through Sept 4th with @stillhousejunkies. Join us on the lawn for some tunes and brews!
